@node "intro" "intro"
@next "usage"
@prev "main"

 @{u}What is "CDDB", and what does ACDB do?@{uu}


In short, the CDDB and ACDB saves you from having to manually type in artist, disc and
track title information for each audio CD you play via your Amiga's CD Audio player.

Each time you play a CD in your Amiga's CD-ROM drive, you can access a "CD DataBase"
through the Internet (located at @{b}http://www.cddb.com@{ub}) for information about that
specific disc. Recognized as the most accurate audio CD identification service on the
Web, CDDB has data on all kinds of music, even CDs with multiple pressings. Best of
all, accessing CDDB is free for your private use.

CDDB (CD DataBase) is an information database containing artist, disc title, track
titles, and other information for digital audio compact discs. Over time, this archive
has grown to contain a substantial collection of CD information and is continuing to
grow at a rapid rate. This database can be accessed by applications via the CDDB server
hosts that have been set up on the Internet around the world.

The CDDB data format and the CDDB servers are designed to be open, and are used by many
client applications requiring CD information. CDDB has become the de facto standard for
Internet access of compact disc information.

ACDB (Amiga CD dataBase) retrieves this information for any CD that you request. It
then saves these files in a format (SCDP file format) that most Amiga CD players can
read.

Currently, configuration of ACDB is only via icon TOOLTYPES.

@endnode

@node "usage" "Usage"
@next "tool"
@prev "intro"

 @{u}Steps in using ACDB:@{uu}


 1. Configure the @{"tooltypes" link "tool" 0} to match your system settings.
 
 2. Start it from Workbench by double-clicking the ACDB icon.
 
 3. When ACDB is started, a small window will open.

 4. You must first collect special file id's for every CD you have by clicking
    on the 'Write ID' gadget. Note: all idfiles will be saved in the TEMP dir.

 5. When you're done, you must go 'online' by clicking 'Download'.

 6. ACDB will then download all descriptions for each id file found in TEMP.

 7. If multiple matches are found (or inexact matches) ACDB will download
    all available descriptions with filename convention IDxxxxxx.yy
    where IDxxxxxx is the normal ID file (SCDP format) and yy is the number of
    (cd-description) copy. After downloading, you must check these files and
    rename them manually or delete them.

 8. After a successful download, all files in TEMP will be deleted (see also
    CLEANTEMP tooltype) -- some errors can break the download process, but
    most of them can only rename idfiles (in TEMP dir) to identify errors
    (IDxxxxxxx.not found or IDxxxxxxx.corrupt).

 9. You can cancel the download by pressing the "Abort" gadget, but note that
    there may be some delay before it quits -- this is normal.

 10. ACDB saves the window position and size in ENV:acdb so you could copy
     this file to ENVARC: and will therefore be used as the defaults.

 11. When started from CLI, pressing CTRL-D will abort description
     downloads, CTRL-F will uniconify ACDB, and CTRL-C will quit.
@endnode

@node "tool" "Tooltypes"
@next "arexx"
@prev "main"

 @{u}Tooltypes:@{uu}


 @{b}DEVICE@{ub}=your_cd_device (default: cd.device)

 @{b}UNIT@{ub}=device_unit (default: 0)

 @{b}HOST@{ub}=cddb_host (default: www.cddb.com) - you can obtain a list of cddb
 hosts near you by executing the included acdb_hosts program

 @{b}PORT@{ub}=cddb_port (default: 80)

 @{b}CDTIME@{ub}=yes|NO
 inserts cdtime in cd description file (CDID), (default: NO)

 @{b}TRACKTIME@{ub}=yes|NO
 insert time for each track (in description file CDID), (default: NO)

 @{b}CLEANTEMP@{ub}=YES|no
 after successfully downloading the file, ACDB will delete unused files from
 the TEMP directory, (default: YES)

 @{b}TEMP@{ub}=dir (default: PROGDIR:temp) - directory where all temporary
 files (grabbed from CD's) will be saved

 @{b}DISKS@{ub}=dir (default: PROGDIR:disks) - directory where ready CDID files
 will be saved

 @{b}ICONFILE@{ub}=file (default: PROGDIR:acdb) - icon file name (without .info) that
 will be used when iconified

 @{b}PUBSCREEN@{ub}=screen_name (default: Workbench) - defines on which screen acdb
 will open it's window
@endnode

@node "arexx" "ARexx Commands"
@next "bugs"
@prev "tool"

 @{u}ARexx Commands:@{uu}


 @{b}AREXX@{ub} - arexxport name is ACDB[.x] (ACDB, ACDB.1, ACDB.2, ...)

 @{b}TRAY IN@{ub} - load tray

 @{b}TRAY OUT@{ub} - eject tray

 @{b}CDID STORE@{ub} - save idfile in TEMP dir

 @{b}CDID FORCE STORE@{ub} - save idfile in TEMP dir without checking for the same
                    file in DISKS dir

 @{b}CDID DOWNLOAD@{ub} - download description from internet for cd in drive

 @{b}DOWNLOAD IDFILE@{ub} - download description for IDFILE (with path)
 
 @{b}DOWNLOAD ALL@{ub} - download descriptions for all idfiles from TEMP dir

 @{b}GET COMMANDLIST@{ub}
 @{b}GET AUTHOR@{ub}
 @{b}GET COPYRIGHT@{ub}
 @{b}GET VERSION@{ub}
 @{b}GET LASTERROR@{ub}

 @{b}AREXX ERROR CONDITIONS:@{ub}
 
 1 - TRUE
 0 - FALSE (additional information from GET LASTERROR command)
@endnode

